main event: A civilian reported seeing a shiny metal cone-shaped object with short wings over York, Pennsylvania on November 11, 1966.
interesting points: The witness saw the object disappear behind a row of houses on their street.
The witness saw the object again the next day, and it appeared to be about a mile away in the sky and about an inch long.
The witness estimated the object was directly above a telephone pole that was 30 feet high from the ground.
The witness reported the sighting to the Air Force's Project Blue Book investigation.
The witness also sent a copy of the report to the Aerial Phenomena Research Organization (APRO).
sighted object: shiny metal cone-shaped object with short wings
